        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 12:05PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 1204 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Yorkville, or 9 miles
west of Dallas, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Dallas, Hiram, Braswell, Yorkville, Cross Roads, Burnt Hickory Ridge,
Draketown, Eubank Lake, New Hope, and New Georgia.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
